				<h2>Initiative: Lake's Crossing</h2>
				<h4>Description (Summary)</h4>
				<p>During the 77th Legislative Session, both the Governor and Legislature supported providing ten additional forensic mental health beds for the Lake’s Crossing Facility. These additional beds will become available by remodeling a portion of the Dini-Townsend Psychiatric Hospital on the Northern Nevada Adult Mental Health (NNAMHS) campus. This project would increase the number of available forensic beds from 66 to 76. Twenty new staff would be needed to support this expansion. The goal of the expansion is to reduce the length of time that mentally ill individuals wait in jails for transfer to the forensic mental health facility for competency evaluation and restorative treatment.</p>
				<h4>Justification (Summary)</h4>
				<p>Population growth, changes in court procedures, and other factors have led to increases in the number of individuals requiring treatment at Lake’s Crossing, the state’s only forensic mental health facility. At the same time, the length of stay for discharged patients at Lake’s has increased from an average of 68 days in Fiscal Year 2009 to 98 days in Fiscal Year 2013.</p>
